== an exact prefix hides the case-insensitive match:
makefile.bak
== a lowercase token corrects to the uppercase name when nothing prefixes exactly:
README
== an uppercase byte forces a case-sensitive match:
README
== a subsequence matches a name-like token of two or more bytes:
foo_bar_baz
== a single byte does not fuzzy match, only its exact prefixes:
plain.txt
